		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Fordism</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><b>Fordism</b>, named after <a href="/wiki/Henry_Ford" title="Henry Ford">Henry Ford</a>, refers to various <a href="/wiki/Social_theory" title="Social theory">social theories</a> about production and related socio-economic phenomena.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> It has varying but related meanings in different fields, as well as for Marxist and non-Marxist scholars.</p>
